"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Detect and repair disconnected metadata branches during CLI commands\n\n## Context\n\nPR #511 prevents the empty-orphan bug going forward, but users who already hit the bug and continued working have a local `entire/checkpoints/v1` with real checkpoint data on a completely disconnected history from remote (no common ancestor). Currently PR #518 handles this in `EnsureMetadataBranch` during `entire enable`, but this is the wrong place ﻗ°½ detection should happen during the CLI commands that actually need the metadata branch (explain, rewind, resume, etc.).\n\n**Diverged is fine** ﻗ°½ local and remote share a common ancestor but each has unique commits. This is normal multi-dev flow, handled by the push path's tree merge. **Disconnected is the bug state** ﻗ°½ no common ancestor, only caused by the empty-orphan bug. This needs detection and repair.\n\n## Approach\n\n### Detection\n\nCheck if local and remote `entire/checkpoints/v1` are disconnected using `git merge-base`:\n\n```\ngit merge-base <local-hash> <remote-hash>\n```\n- Exit 0 ﻗ│φ shares ancestry (diverged or one is ancestor of other) ﻗ│φ no action\n- Exit non-zero, no output ﻗ│φ disconnected ﻗ│φ repair needed\n\n### Repair: cherry-pick local commits onto remote tip\n\n1. Walk local branch from tip to root, collect commits (oldest-first)\n2. Skip the initial empty orphan commit (empty tree, no useful data)\n3. Reset local branch to remote tip\n4. For each local commit:\n   - Compute new entries: flatten commit's tree, subtract parent's tree entries\n   - Apply new entries onto current tip's tree\n   - Create new commit preserving original message/author\n5. Update local branch ref\n\nThis works because checkpoint shards are unique paths (`<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/`) ﻗ°½ cherry-picks always apply cleanly. Preserves linear commit history and individual commit messages.\n\n### Where detection runs\n\n**Once per process**, triggered at the strategy layer when the checkpoint store is first accessed. Uses `sync.Once` to avoid redundant `git merge-base` calls.\n\n**Call sites:**\n1. `ManualCommitStrategy.getCheckpointStore()` (`manual_commit.go:47`) ﻗ°½ covers all strategy-mediated reads and writes (explain, rewind, resume, clean, condensation)\n2. `getBranchCheckpoints()` (`explain.go:888`) ﻗ°½ bypasses strategy, creates own GitStore\n3. `ListCheckpoints()` (`strategy/common.go:112`) ﻗ°½ opens own repo, reads branch directly\n\n### User-facing output\n\n```\n[entire] Detected disconnected session metadata (local and remote share no common ancestor)\n[entire] Cherry-picking 3 local checkpoint(s) onto remote...\n[entire] Done ﻗ°½ all local and remote checkpoints preserved\n```\n\n## Files to modify\n\n### New file: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/metadata_reconcile.go`\n\nDetection + cherry-pick repair:\n\n- `ReconcileDisconnectedMetadataBranch(repo *git.Repository) error` ﻗ°½ main function\n- `isDisconnected(repoPath, hashA, hashB string) bool` ﻗ°½ uses `git merge-base` (not `--is-ancestor`)\n- `collectCommitChain(repo, ref) []*object.Commit` ﻗ°½ walks parents to root, returns oldest-first\n- `cherryPickOnto(repo, base plumbing.Hash, commits []*object.Commit) (plumbing.Hash, error)` ﻗ°½ applies each commit's new entries onto base\n\nReuses: `checkpoint.FlattenTree()`, `checkpoint.BuildTreeFromEntries()`, `GetGitAuthorFromRepo()`\n\n### New file: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/metadata_reconcile_test.go`\n\nTests using existing `initBareWithMetadataBranch` and `cloneWithConfig` helpers:\n\n- `TestReconcileDisconnected_NoRemote` ﻗ°½ no-op\n- `TestReconcileDisconnected_NoLocal` ﻗ°½ no-op\n- `TestReconcileDisconnected_SameHash` ﻗ°½ no-op\n- `TestReconcileDisconnected_SharedAncestry` ﻗ°½ no-op (diverged, not disconnected)\n- `TestReconcileDisconnected_Disconnected` ﻗ°½ creates disconnected orphan with local checkpoint, verifies after repair: linear history on top of remote, both local and remote data present\n- `TestReconcileDisconnected_MultipleLocalCheckpoints` ﻗ°½ 3 local commits, all cherry-picked\n\n### Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go`\n\n- Add package-level `sync.Once` gate: `ensureMetadataReconciled(repo)`\n- Export: `EnsureMetadataReconciled(repo *git.Repository) error` ﻗ°½ for callers outside strategy package\n- Remove `syncMetadataBranch` call from `EnsureMetadataBranch` (move that logic to the new reconcile function)\n- Keep `isAncestorCLI` ﻗ°½ still useful for the fast-forward case\n- Add reconciliation call to `ListCheckpoints()`\n\n### Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit.go`\n\nIn `getCheckpointStore()`, add after `OpenRepository`:\n```go\nif err := ensureMetadataReconciled(repo); err != nil {\n    fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"[entire] Warning: ٪v\\n\", err)\n}\n```\n\n### Modify: `cmd/entire/cli/explain.go`\n\nIn `getBranchCheckpoints()`, add before `checkpoint.NewGitStore(repo)`:\n```go\nif err := strategy.EnsureMetadataReconciled(repo); err != nil {\n    // Log but don't fail ﻗ°½ reads may still work\n}\n```\n\n## What happens in `EnsureMetadataBranch` after this change\n\n`EnsureMetadataBranch` (called during `enable`) keeps only:\n- Create local from remote when local doesn't exist (PR #511)\n- Replace empty orphan with remote (PR #516)\n- Create empty orphan when neither exists\n- Error handling for non-ref-not-found errors\n\nThe disconnected/diverged reconciliation logic (`syncMetadataBranch`) is removed ﻗ°½ that responsibility moves to `ReconcileDisconnectedMetadataBranch`.\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\n```\n\nSpecific tests:\n```bash\ngo test ./cmd/entire/cli/strategy/ -run TestReconcileDisconnected -v\n```\n\nManual verification:\n1. Clone repo with remote checkpoints\n2. Create disconnected local branch (orphan with different data)\n3. Run `go run ./cmd/entire explain --no-pager --commit <hash>`\n4. Verify reconciliation message appears and explain succeeds\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/dvydra/.claude/projects/-Users-dvydra-src-cli/229c0af5-5604-44a0-a6ae-795bdcb0d95b.jsonl\n\n---\n\ncreate the PR"